r\n</tr>\r\n<tr class=\"sub-heatbl\">\r\n<td>From</td>\r\n<td>To</td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>0</td>\r\n<td>50,000,000</td>\r\n<td>0.05%</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>50,000,001</td>\r\n<td>100,000,000</td>\r\n<td>0.04%</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>100,000,001</td>\r\n<td>200,000,000</td>\r\n<td>0.035%</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>200,000,001</td>\r\n<td>Any Value</td>\r\n<td>0.03%</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p class=\"mt30\">All rates are as percent of transaction value. In case of Options - Sum of transaction values as per ((Strike price + Premium) * lot size)) will be considered as turnover during the month. Brokerage Rate is on a per lot basis</p>\r\n<h4 class=\"procedures-hea terms-gap\">Additional terms applicable to Multi-Tier (variable) brokerage plan :-</h4>\r\n<ul class=\"procedure-plices\">\r\n<li>Brokerage is charged at rates applicable for the minimum turnover slab, on a daily basis.</li>\r\n<li>Applicable Statutory charges are levied separately e.g. Service Tax, STT, Stamp Duty, Exchange Transaction Charges, SEBI turnover charges etc.</li>\r\n<li>Turnover is computed from start of the calendar month or date of enrolment for the plan whichever is later. The last date for the month considered for brokerage purposes will always be the last date of that calendar month.</li>\r\n<li>Refund is limited to the amount of brokerage and no other charges will be refunded.</li>\r\n<li>Equity-Encash transactions will be charged as per fixed brokerage plan.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4 class=\"procedures-hea terms-gap\">Additional Terms applicable to both Fixed and Multi-Tier (Variable) brokerage plans :</h4>\r\n<ul class=\"procedure-plices\">\r\n<li>Trading account opening charges are Rs. 999/- (including recovery of charges incurred on franking/stamping of documents).</li>\r\n<li>Stamp duty, Service Tax, Securities Transaction Tax (STT), Exchange Transaction charges are charged as per the rates applicable.</li>\r\n<li>Brokerage will be charged as per applicable rate subject to a minimum of Rs.20/- per executed order and a maximum of 2.5%. In case the minimum brokerage calculated comes to more than 2.5%, then the amount that will be charged as a brokerage will be limited to 2.5%. For securities quoting upto Rs. 10.00 per share, Brokerage will be charged at Rs. 0.03 per share.</li>\r\n<li>The rates provided in this schedule are subject to change with 15 (Fifteen) days prior intimation.</li>\r\n<li>Any penalty levied by Exchanges on the client\'s positions shall be recovered from the client\'s account (eg. penalty for short collection of margin).</li>\r\n<li>In case of delay in payment of trading related issues, Delayed payment penalty will be charged at the rate of 18% per annum.</li>\r\n<li>Delivery includes transaction in Cash &amp; E-margin and Intraday includes transaction in Intraday &amp; Cover.</li>\r\n<li>Cash/Delivery transactions squared off on the same day will be charged brokerage at rates applicable for Intraday trades.</li>\r\n<li>Intrinsic Value for call option is Spot Price  Strike Price and for put options it is Strike Price  Spot Price.</li>\r\n<li>Futures Expiry Charges: Futures Expiry charges (comprising of stamp duty etc.) are levied on the value of outstanding position (Outstanding Position * Settlement Price).</li>\r\n<li>Exercise/Assignment Charges (comprising of stamp duty, STT etc.) are levied on the Settlement value of the option. Exchange Transaction Charges on Options trades will be computed on premium amount.</li>\r\n<li>All Intraday and E-margin transactions that are converted to delivery will be charged brokerages as applicable to Cash/Delivery trades.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4 class=\"procedures-hea terms-gap\">Other Terms and Conditions:</h4>\r\n<ul class=\"procedure-plices\">\r\n<li>Service tax is levied at 14.50% of the brokerage &amp; Exchange transaction charges.</li>\r\n<li>SEBI Turnover Charges: SEBI Turnover charges are levied at 0.0001% of turnover.</li>\r\n<li>Brokerage is computed on per share basis and is rounded off to the nearest paise, subject to a minimum brokerage of 1 paise per share.</li>\r\n<li>System abuse charges, if any, as levied by Exchange(s) will be recovered from the respective clients.</li>\r\n<li>In case of penny stocks, Brokerage will be charged as per applicable rate subject to minimum of Rs. 20/- per executed order and a maximum of Rs. 0.25 paise per share. In case the minimum brokerage calculated comes to more than Rs. 0.25 paise per share, then the amount that will be charged as a brokerage will be limited to Rs. 0.25 paise per share.</li>\r\n<li>The first ten calls to Trade on Phone service in a calendar month shall be free of any service charge. All the subsequent calls to the Trade on Phone number will be charged @Rs.20.00 per call to the client account.</li>\r\n<li>The mode of sending Contract Notes shall be through emails and posting on website for the client who have opted for ECN.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class=\"clearfix mf-tables mt30\">\r\n<div class=\"policy-tables\">\r\n<table width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr class=\"tb-heading\">\r\n<td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Mutual Funds  Distribution (MFD)</strong></td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\">Purchase</td>\r\n<td>Redemption</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\">Rs. 75/-</td>\r\n<td>Nil</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\"></td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\">SIP (Charge per transaction)</td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\">Purchase</td>\r\n<td>Redemption</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\">Rs. 25 or 1.5%, whichever is lower</td>\r\n<td>NA</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"policy-tables righ-proced\">\r\n<table width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr class=\"tb-heading\">\r\n<td colspan=\"2\"><strong>Mutual Funds  Exchange (MFE)</strong></td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\">Lumpsum Investment (Charge per transaction)</td